canMove

public boolean canMove(java.util.Collection<Robot> allRobots,
                       Robot robot)
This method should be called before move(Robot robot) to check whether Robot can be moved to next Location or not? LeftMove and RightMove classes are simply returning true from canMove() method because in those moves (left & right) Coordinate of Robot will not change. For example usage see BaseRobot

Specified by:
canMove in class Move
Parameters:
allRobots - all Robot(s) under a Robot controlling system/space.
robot -
Returns:
boolean Whether Robot can be moved to next Location or not?

LeftMove, RightMove, StepMove
